@sodacan

As of the list of restrictions for an external user almost all of them are broken when the user has access to the project access token. The user can now view all internal projects as any regular internal user. More than that, the user can now create Issues in the name of the token (name of token is transferred to name of bot user)
{F1312936}
and also create internal snippets that will show up in other users search/explore lists
{F1312937}
{F1312935}
These actions can be used to try to get a leverage inside the organization. As in image 1 the user can ask to be added to internal projects with private repositories etc. Or create snippets where the user posts "example configuration files" or similar.
